    <details>
      <summary>How does the heavy debt load impact the DCF?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">The $9.6B in total debt directly reduces the Equity Value. We calculate Enterprise Value from the future cash flows, then subtract Net Debt (-$8.47B) to find what is left for shareholders. High debt also justifies our slightly elevated 9.5% discount rate.</div>
    </details>
